node.title: Victoria records 1,232 new local COVID-19 cases and nine deaths
node.alt: Health workers conduct COVID tests at drive-in centre
node.description: There are now 11,224 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 580 people have died during the state's current outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,232\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and nine\u00a0deaths as health authorities continue to investigate possible cases of the Omicron variant in Melbourne.\u00a0", "One case of Omicron was confirmed in hotel quarantine yesterday, while two potential community\u00a0cases\u00a0in Melbourne's west and south-east are undergoing genomic testing.", "There are 11,224\u00a0active cases of COVID-19\u00a0in Victoria, and 580\u00a0people have died during the state's current\u00a0outbreak.\u00a0", "There are 315\u00a0people in hospital with the virus, of whom 52\u00a0are in intensive care and 27\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 44\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new COVID-19 cases were detected from 71,178\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,647\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has\u00a0fully vaccinated more than 91\u00a0per cent of its population aged 12 and over.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
